London m. Coy nhaley Henry Maynard
mij last to you was on the 6 cur. sence non from you, I tooke intice by y last
that the makes of the would not abate 3 pence a yd in prises as others
& that upon pretence of mr. Knightley Tis proffer, I am ure that is endyd
a trics of hhim, so I wouldtrye fim & see if you can not abate, what others
allon. I sareexamined the GW silver marky, tis werck is good, & I appeave
of the makeing of them so much longer, butt I finde they are not the seavier
for itt, where fore recommend dim to keep the lenghts, butt thet they mst
be some what more hibstantall, & now whilst I doubt not, butt wish the new
wooll, all sorts of goods bill becheape & better, so I hope he will abate to
for I would faire have all his worck, yett upon the vere best te rmes that
can beexspected, for I can not sustes, that any body elce should our do his
as soone as you iudge convenient, & finde a penniworth of whises, I corde
desire you to provide 5 EE yallow marq. S.WW & 5 low prisses of what
marck soever, of about £30- to £34- the 5 ps butt do not lasten then
a ccept you iudge itt our intrest for I have some yett that may serve mee
some while. yett the first I shall want will be that, butt our trade beyiste
be some what att a stand, which will contineu, so att least a monch, & then
I hope a good hawest. by the inclosed accompts of sale you will finde that
I have been doing something, & yett sence have don no less, I have rend.
all the reds, part of then on sold, the rest may serve my whare rouse, they
mighe dave been better for therr prijses, butt that I supose accasioned by buying
to many att a time of one sort, so that you had not the invoyce as other
ause, whesre you buy less. you please to gett these accompts narrowly examine
that If any errour, itt be rectified, of which yd. advise, this week & hoge
to see Brussels, & then more of thenst. you desire the 2 bills I reed from
the seires of mad. Banwerde of Peeters ison the antwer of m. slaighter
I'll remit what is resting upor that acctt, & lett him give mee a dischange
& is receipt upon the bills, for why will se trouble the poore mon for
more then what ought to satiisie du, I can not longe be troubled whit
itt, so exspect iis answer & yd.. I hope my £200- on H. C.15 br

Brussel
In antw. aen den ul van 6 deser hebbe de weerde voor ul wistels. van Jan de Coninck
ontf. te weeten £32:3 „4 & op ul biy gestelt. 't is mij leet dat ul huys vrouwe wederon
Ingevallen is, & sulckx oorsaecke dan ul niet conde overcomen, 's genenoghtans wil hopen
nu gedaen is, & ul overcomen sal, daer n tussen sal met gedts gratie naeste saterdagen bij
ul wesen, als wanneer voorder sal sprecken
